Revision 1.48 by Eric Piton
Date: March 04, 2025
Description: A fully self-sufficient PC for office tasks and intensive gaming, generating power from CPU/GPU heat via ferrofluid, copper tubing, and TEG modules. Self-sufficient at idle, 50%, and 100% loads post-boot, with excess stored in a 200 Wh battery. Breaks even in ~2.84 years vs. traditional PCs. Built with real-world parts available today, maximizing ferrofluid shelf life (~5+ years).

