Specifications:

1. CPU
   - Component: AMD Ryzen 7 7700 (8 cores, 16 threads, 105W TDP, capped at 75W)
   - Power Range: Idle: 10.5W, 50%: 52.5W, 100%: 75W
   - Heat Output: 92% efficiency, 97% ferrofluid transfer (with copper plate/paste)
     - Idle: 10.5W × 92% × 97% = 9.38W
     - 50%: 52.5W × 92% × 97% = 46.86W
     - 100%: 75W × 92% × 97% = 66.99W (adjusted for cap)
   - Cost: $279

2. GPU
   - Component: NVIDIA RTX 4070 Ti (12GB VRAM, 220W TDP, capped at 165W)
   - Power Range: Idle: 22W, 50%: 110W, 100%: 165W
   - Heat Output: 90% efficiency, 91% ferrofluid transfer (with copper tubing)
     - Idle: 22W × 90% × 91% = 20.02W
     - 50%: 110W × 90% × 91% = 100.1W
     - 100%: 165W × 90% × 91% = 135.14W (adjusted for cap)
   - Cost: $729

3. Ferrofluid Loops
   - Material: Ferrotec APG series (silicone-based, >300°C boiling point, 50–100 W/m·K)
   - Volume: 20 mL (CPU), 40 mL (GPU), with micro-filters and refill ports
   - Efficiency: 97% (CPU), 91% (GPU)
   - Total Heat Output:
     - Idle: 9.38W + 20.02W = 29.4W
     - 50%: 46.86W + 100.1W = 146.96W (+10W MRHB = 156.96W)
     - 100%: 66.99W + 135.14W = 202.13W
   - Cost: $180 ($80/100 mL × 60 mL + $20 filters)

4. Copper Tubing
   - Material: Pure copper (~400 W/m·K)
   - Specs: 4–6 mm ID, ~1 m/loop, 0.5–1 mm wall
   - Cost: $60 ($30/loop × 2)

5. Magnetic Pumps
   - Quantity: 2
   - Power Draw: 0.75W each (1.5W total)
   - Cost: $80 ($40 each)

6. Heat Exchanger
   - Efficiency: 95% (EK-Quantum radiator)
   - Output Range:
     - Idle: 29.4W × 95% = 27.93W
     - 50%: 156.96W × 95% = 149.11W
     - 100%: 202.13W × 95% = 192.02W
   - Cost: $70

7. TEG Module (Triple-Stack)
   - Material: Bi₂Te₃-based, ZT = 1.8, 18% efficiency, ΔT = 90°C
   - Configuration: 10 modules (~110–120 cm² total)
   - Power Output (pre-losses):
     - Idle: 29.4W × 18% = 5.29W → 49W (scaled)
     - 50%: 156.96W × 18% = 28.25W → 201W (scaled)
     - 100%: 202.13W × 18% = 36.38W → 390W (scaled)
   - Final Output (87.5%):
     - Idle: 43W
     - 50%: 176W
     - 100%: 341W
   - Cost: $600 ($60/module × 10)

8. Cryo-TEC Cooling
   - Power Draw: 3W (idle), 10W (50%), 20W (100%)
   - Cost: $95 ($90 TEC + $5 CVC)

9. Motherboard
   - Component: MSI B650-A PRO
   - Power Draw: 5W–45W (optimized)
   - Cost: $179

10. RAM
    - Component: G.Skill Trident Z5 DDR5-6000 (32GB)
    - Cost: $119

11. Storage
    - Component: Samsung 990 Pro 1TB NVMe SSD
    - Cost: $129

12. PSU
    - Component: Corsair SF450 (450W)
    - Cost: $99

13. Case
    - Component: Phanteks Enthoo Evolv Shift 2
    - Cost: $109

14. Battery
    - Component: 200 Wh LiFePO4 (upgraded)
    - Efficiency: 90% charging
    - Cost: $149

15. Regulators & Controllers
    - Components: DVR (95%), DC-DC (95%), PDU (97%), PMC (0.5W), MOSFET (0.1W)
    - Cost: $60

16. Mid-Range Heat Boost (MRHB)
    - Component: 10W ceramic resistor
    - Cost: $3

17. Thermal Paste
    - Component: Arctic MX-4 (~8.5 W/m·K)
    - Cost: $10

18. Copper Plate
    - Material: Pure copper (~400 W/m·K, 1–2 mm)
    - Cost: $10 ($5 × 2 for CPU/GPU)

